# agent.ai — Root Instruction for AI Coding Agents

Read and obey `AGENTS.md` before doing any work.

Hard rules:

1. Work on one task only.
2. Mark the task as `[-] In Progress` in `TASKS.md` before editing code.
3. Append a start log to `WORK_LOG.md` before editing code.
4. Update `HANDOFF.md` with the current task.
5. Never store original images in R2.
6. Only store final compressed watermarked attachments in R2 binding `LOGS`.
7. Use existing D1 binding `DB`; do not create a new database.
8. Table names must use `HL_` prefix and no underscore after prefix.
9. Field names must be camelCase.
10. AI Vision must timeout at 5000 ms and fall back to manual input.
11. Manual override is mandatory.
12. Medical status must come from `HL_metricRules`, not from AI.
13. AI must not diagnose, prescribe, or modify medication dosage.
14. Telegram push after submit must not block measurement save.
15. After every completed task, update relevant documentation.
16. Never delete previous work logs.

Completion checklist:

```text
[ ] Code complete
[ ] Validation run
[ ] Docs updated
[ ] TASKS.md updated
[ ] WORK_LOG.md updated
[ ] HANDOFF.md updated
[ ] Known issues documented
```
